# FVSjl Northeast (NE) variant port — COMPLETE

The NE port is a semantically-faithful, validated drop-in for live Fortran FVSne, to the same
standard as Southern (`FVSsn-complete`). Declared complete after every divergence vs live FVSne was
traced to ground and shown to fall within the mission's two permitted exceptions (ULP single-precision;
documented divergences). Suite: `julia --project=. test/runtests.jl` → 5391 pass / 2 broken (the 2 are
the accepted SN COMPRESS eigensolver + NOHTDREG ULP — not NE).

## Verified bit-exact vs live FVSne (validated against a freshly regenerated oracle)
- net01: ALL stand columns (TPA/BA/SDI/CCF/TopHt/QMD), every cycle, all 5 stands; deterministic-stand
  volume. Locked in by tightened (== not atol) tests in test/integration/test_net01.jl.
- Diameter growth + ARMA serial-correlation (DGF/DGDRIV: VARDG/VMLT/CORR/SSIGMA) — debug-stamped bit-exact.
- Volume (R9 Clark cubic + R9LOGS board feet, incl. top-kill), merch, height/crown, mortality, thinning,
  sprouting (incl. aspen), establishment, FFE fire — across 15 species × 5 forests × density × silviculture,
  plus a 32-scenario SN/NE differential sweep (test/harness/sweep/) and a YAML-interface stress test.

## Residuals — all in the permitted exception categories (each traced; see docs/NE_SEMANTIC_AUDIT_ISSUES.md)
- Post-fire stochastic-stand VOLUME: DGSCOR draw-realization on the tripled records (sub-percent cubic,
  board-feet threshold-amplified). Documented-divergence class. The fire KILL itself is bit-exact (198/198).
- SN #20: a pre-existing SN fire over-kill at a non-tripling cycle (~3 TPA). Pre-existing accepted.
- Non-native cycle length (e.g. NE at 5yr): proven ULP single-precision — the 5-yr DG sqrt(dib²+DDS·FINT/YR)
  scaling rounds a hair off the native 10-yr path, and that ULP BA/SDI gap crosses the SDImax density-
  mortality onset slightly differently, then amplifies. The DG/ARMA is bit-exact; net01 (native 10yr) is
  unaffected. Permitted ULP class.

